jobs.description:
IT Infrastructure Management:
Ensure the network infrastructure (LAN, WAN, Wi-Fi) operates reliably and securely throughout the school;
Manage and maintain the Analog and VoIP telephone systems, as well as the school's servers, data storage, backup, and recovery systems;
Ensure hardware devices such as servers and network equipment (APs, switches) are installed, maintained, and repaired promptly.
Software System Management:
Install, configure, and manage the necessary software systems for educational and administrative operations in the school;
Ensure the stability and security of learning management systems (LMS), student information systems (SIS), and other supporting software.
Information Security:
Develop and implement security policies to protect sensitive data of students, teachers, and staff;
Manage firewall systems, antivirus software, online gaming, and other security measures to prevent external attacks.
Technical Support:
Provide technical support to teachers, students, and staff in the school;
Guide and train staff on how to use IT systems and software.
System Maintenance and Upgrades:
Plan and implement projects to upgrade the school's IT infrastructure;
Monitor, test, and ensure that the hardware and software in use are operating effectively, performing regular maintenance, and upgrading as needed.
Data Storage and Backup Management:
Set up and manage data storage systems, ensuring data security and availability;
Implement backup and data recovery plans to ensure continuous system operation and prevent data loss.
Coordination with Vendors:
Work with partners and vendors to maintain and repair equipment and systems as needed;
Manage contracts, prepare repair proposals, and service requests with vendors related to hardware, software, and IT support services.
User Training and Support:
Organize training sessions on information technology for teachers, staff, and students to enhance the effective use of IT systems;
Provide end-user support for using software, IT tools, and troubleshooting related issues.

jobs.requirements:
Degree in Information Technology Management or any related fields;
Have at least 3 years of experience in similar positions or relevant jobs;
Hands on experience in networking, routing and switch;
Excellent knowledge of best practices around management, control, and monitoring of IT infrastructure.
Ability to set up and configure server hardware;
Familiarity with backup and recovery methodologies;
Good communication in English.

